<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><title>$ command line ruby cheat sheets</title><link charset="utf-8" href="/style.css" media="screen" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" /></head><body><div class="main"><div class="header"><h1><a href="/">cheat sheets.</a></h1><code class="header">$ command line ruby cheat sheets</code></div></div><div class="content"><pre>How do I control my Twitter through tweet.IM?
Just type your Twitter message to twitter.tweet.im or your-username.tweet.im and it will appear in your timeline. Type a single keyword help to see more commands. Current commands include:

@username message — public reply/send a message to this person

d username message — sends a direct message to this person


f username — follow this person

u username — unfollow this person


p username — information on user profile

ing — list people you follow (following)

ers &amp;mdashl list people that follow you (followers)


ss — show saved searches

sd searchname — delete saved search

sa query — save a search query


ts — show your current tweet mode: on, off or auto

tm mode — set tweet mode where mode is:

    on - always receive tweets

    off - never receive tweets

    auto - receive tweets depending on your current status</pre></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="footer">Powered by <a href="http://www.sinatrarb.com/">Sinatra</a>,
<a href="http://puma.io/">Puma</a> and, to a lesser extent,
